Adolf Wiklund (5 June 1879 in Långserud, Värmland – 2 April 1950 in Stockholm) was a Swedish composer and conductor.
His debut as a piano soloist came in 1902 playing his own Konsertstycke in C major, Op 1.
After 1911 he worked mainly as a conductor.
He conducted the Swedish Royal Orchestra from 1911 to 1924, he was director of the Royal Swedish Opera in 1923, and he served as principal conductor of the Stockholm Concert Society until 1938.
